{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/Readium\/documentation\/Readium","doc:\/\/Readium\/documentation\/Readium\/NavigatorOverview"]]},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"anchor":"overview","type":"heading","text":"Overview"},{"name":"Note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"[!NOTE]"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"You cannot change the default font family of a fixed-layout EPUB (with zoomable pages), as it is similar to a PDF or a comic book."}]}],"type":"aside","style":"note"},{"level":2,"anchor":"Available-font-families","type":"heading","text":"Available font families"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"iOS ships with a large collection of font families that you can use directly in the EPUB preferences. "},{"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/fonts\/system-fonts\/","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"To improve readability, Readium embeds three additional font families designed for accessibility:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/opendyslexic.org\/"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/Orange-OpenSource\/font-accessible-dfa","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":", by Orange"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/iaolo\/iA-Fonts\/tree\/master\/iA%20Writer%20Duospace","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":", by iA","type":"text"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"You can use all the iOS System Fonts out of the box with the EPUB navigator:","type":"text"}]},{"code":["epubNavigator.submitPreferences(EPUBPreferences(","    fontFamily: \"Palatino\"","))"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Alternatively, extend "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"FontFamily"},{"type":"text","text":" to benefit from the compiler type safety:"}]},{"code":["extension FontFamily {","    public static let palatino: FontFamily = \"Palatino\"","}","","epubNavigator.submitPreferences(EPUBPreferences(","    fontFamily: .palatino","))"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"For your convenience, a number of ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/readium.org\/readium-css\/docs\/CSS09-default_fonts"},{"text":" are pre-declared in the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"FontFamily"},{"text":" type: Iowan Old Style, Palatino, Athelas, Georgia, Helvetica Neue, Seravek and Arial.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Setting-the-available-font-families-in-the-user-interface","level":2,"text":"Setting the available font families in the user interface"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If you build your settings user interface with the EPUB Preferences Editor, you can customize the list of available font families using ","type":"text"},{"code":"with(supportedValues:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["epubPreferencesEditor.fontFamily.with(supportedValues: [","    nil, \/\/ A `nil` value means that the original author font will be used.","    .palatino,","    .helveticaNeue,","    .iaWriterDuospace,","    .accessibleDfA,","    .openDyslexic","])"]},{"type":"heading","anchor":"How-to-add-custom-font-families","level":2,"text":"How to add custom font families?"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"To offer more choices to your users, you must embed and declare custom font families. Use the following steps:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"orderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Get the font files in the desired format, such as .ttf and .otf. "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/fonts.google.com\/","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" is a good source of free fonts."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Add the files to your app target from Xcode.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Declare new extensions for your custom font families to make them first-class citizens. This is optional but convenient."}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["extension FontFamily {","    public static let literata: FontFamily = \"Literata\"","    public static let atkinsonHyperlegible: FontFamily = \"Atkinson Hyperlegible\"","}"],"syntax":"swift"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Configure the EPUB navigator with a declaration of the font faces for all the additional font families."}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["let resources = FileURL(url: Bundle.main.resourceURL!)!","let navigator = try EPUBNavigatorViewController(","    publication: publication,","    initialLocation: locator,","    config: .init(","        fontFamilyDeclarations: [","            CSSFontFamilyDeclaration(","                fontFamily: .literata,","                fontFaces: [","                    \/\/ Literata is a variable font family, so we can provide a font weight range.","                    \/\/ https:\/\/fonts.google.com\/knowledge\/glossary\/variable_fonts","                    CSSFontFace(","                        file: resources.appendingPath(\"Literata-VariableFont_opsz,wght.ttf\", isDirectory: false),","                        style: .normal, weight: .variable(200...900)","                    ),","                    CSSFontFace(","                        file: resources.appendingPath(\"Literata-Italic-VariableFont_opsz,wght.ttf\", isDirectory: false),","                        style: .italic, weight: .variable(200...900)","                    )","                ]","            ).eraseToAnyHTMLFontFamilyDeclaration(),","","            CSSFontFamilyDeclaration(","                fontFamily: .atkinsonHyperlegible,","                fontFaces: [","                    CSSFontFace(","                        file: resources.appendingPath(\"Atkinson-Hyperlegible-Regular.ttf\", isDirectory: false),","                        style: .normal, weight: .standard(.normal)","                    ),","                    CSSFontFace(","                        file: resources.appendingPath(\"Atkinson-Hyperlegible-Italic.ttf\", isDirectory: false),","                        style: .italic, weight: .standard(.normal)","                    ),","                    CSSFontFace(","                        file: resources.appendingPath(\"Atkinson-Hyperlegible-Bold.ttf\", isDirectory: false),","                        style: .normal, weight: .standard(.bold)","                    ),","                    CSSFontFace(","                        file: resources.appendingPath(\"Atkinson-Hyperlegible-BoldItalic.ttf\", isDirectory: false),","                        style: .italic, weight: .standard(.bold)","                    ),","                ]","            ).eraseToAnyHTMLFontFamilyDeclaration()","        ]","    )",")"],"syntax":"swift"}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You are now ready to use your custom font families."}]}]}],"sections":[],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"kind":"article","metadata":{"title":"Font families in the EPUB navigator","role":"article","roleHeading":"Article"},"seeAlsoSections":[{"generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/Readium\/documentation\/Readium\/Navigator","doc:\/\/Readium\/documentation\/Readium\/Preferences","doc:\/\/Readium\/documentation\/Readium\/SwiftUI","doc:\/\/Readium\/documentation\/Readium\/Input"],"anchor":"Essentials","title":"Essentials"}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/Readium\/documentation\/Readium\/EPUB-Fonts","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Readium allows users to customize the font family used to render a reflowable EPUB, by changing the "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"Preferences.md","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"references":{"../Migration%20Guide.md":{"type":"link","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"migration guide"}],"url":"..\/Migration%20Guide.md","identifier":"..\/Migration%20Guide.md","title":"migration guide"},"https://readium.org/readium-css/docs/CSS09-default_fonts":{"url":"https:\/\/readium.org\/readium-css\/docs\/CSS09-default_fonts","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"recommended fonts"}],"identifier":"https:\/\/readium.org\/readium-css\/docs\/CSS09-default_fonts","type":"link","title":"recommended fonts"},"https://opendyslexic.org/":{"type":"link","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"OpenDyslexic"}],"url":"https:\/\/opendyslexic.org\/","identifier":"https:\/\/opendyslexic.org\/","title":"OpenDyslexic"},"https://github.com/iaolo/iA-Fonts/tree/master/iA%20Writer%20Duospace":{"url":"https:\/\/github.com\/iaolo\/iA-Fonts\/tree\/master\/iA%20Writer%20Duospace","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"iA Writer Duospace"}],"identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/iaolo\/iA-Fonts\/tree\/master\/iA%20Writer%20Duospace","type":"link","title":"iA Writer Duospace"},"https://fonts.google.com/":{"type":"link","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Google Fonts"}],"url":"https:\/\/fonts.google.com\/","identifier":"https:\/\/fonts.google.com\/","title":"Google Fonts"},"doc://Readium/documentation/Readium/Input":{"title":"Observing user input","role":"article","url":"\/documentation\/readium\/input","kind":"article","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"In visual publications like EPUB or PDF, users can interact with the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"VisualNavigator"},{"type":"text","text":" instance using gestures, a keyboard, a mouse, a pencil, or a trackpad. When the publication does not override user input events, you may want to intercept them to trigger actions in your user interface. For example, you can turn pages or toggle the navigation bar on taps, or open a bookmarks screen when pressing the Command-Shift-D hotkey."}],"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/Readium\/documentation\/Readium\/Input"},"https://developer.apple.com/documentation/swiftui/uiviewrepresentable":{"type":"link","titleInlineContent":[{"code":"UIViewRepresentable","type":"codeVoice"}],"url":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/swiftui\/uiviewrepresentable","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/swiftui\/uiviewrepresentable","title":"UIViewRepresentable"},"doc://Readium/documentation/Readium/SwiftUI":{"kind":"article","role":"article","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The Navigator is built with UIKit and provides "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"UIViewController"},{"type":"text","text":" implementations. Nevertheless, you can integrate them into a SwiftUI view hierarchy using Apple’s "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/swiftui\/uiviewrepresentable","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"title":"Integrating the Navigator with SwiftUI","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/readium\/swiftui","identifier":"doc:\/\/Readium\/documentation\/Readium\/SwiftUI"},"doc://Readium/documentation/Readium/Preferences":{"kind":"article","title":"Configuring the Navigator","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/Readium\/documentation\/Readium\/Preferences","role":"article","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Take a look at the "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"..\/Migration%20Guide.md"},{"type":"text","text":" if you are already using the legacy EPUB settings."}],"url":"\/documentation\/readium\/preferences"},"https://github.com/Orange-OpenSource/font-accessible-dfa":{"url":"https:\/\/github.com\/Orange-OpenSource\/font-accessible-dfa","titleInlineContent":[{"text":"AccessibleDfA","type":"text"}],"title":"AccessibleDfA","type":"link","identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/Orange-OpenSource\/font-accessible-dfa"},"https://developer.apple.com/fonts/system-fonts/":{"url":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/fonts\/system-fonts\/","titleInlineContent":[{"text":"Take a look at the Apple catalog of System Fonts","type":"text"}],"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/fonts\/system-fonts\/","type":"link","title":"Take a look at the Apple catalog of System Fonts"},"doc://Readium/documentation/Readium/NavigatorOverview":{"title":"Navigator Overview","role":"article","url":"\/documentation\/readium\/navigatoroverview","kind":"article","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/Readium\/documentation\/Readium\/NavigatorOverview","abstract":[{"text":"Learn about the architecture, configuration, and usage of the Readium Navigator.","type":"text"}]},"doc://Readium/documentation/Readium/Navigator":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/Readium\/documentation\/Readium\/Navigator","url":"\/documentation\/readium\/navigator","title":"Navigator","kind":"article","role":"article","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"You can use a Readium Navigator to present the publication to the user. The "},{"code":"Navigator","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" renders resources on the screen and offers APIs and user interactions for navigating the contents."}],"type":"topic"},"doc://Readium/documentation/Readium":{"url":"\/documentation\/readium","role":"collection","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The Readium Swift Toolkit is a toolkit for ebooks, audiobooks, and comics written in Swift & Kotlin."}],"type":"topic","kind":"article","title":"Readium","identifier":"doc:\/\/Readium\/documentation\/Readium"}}}